    "recap_headline": "Rice University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Phoenix-\nSaint Mary's exploded for 11 runs in the final three innings to down Rice 11-6 on Sunday afternoon at Brazell Field at GCU Ballpark.\nHow it Happened:\nThe Owls broke on top in the third with their eighth inning with at least three runs \u00a0in the four games at Brazell Field.\nHiram Bocachica Jr.\nstroked a single to left and moved to third on\nColin Robson's\nfourth double of the weekend.\nJC Davis\nlofted a single to left to score Bocachica with the game's first run.\nPaul Smith\nloaded the bases with a walk and then Robson and Davis came home on back-to-back sacrifice flies by\nGaret Boehm\nand\nKutter-Gage Webb\n. \u00a0Sanders allowed back-to-back singles to open the third but picked both runners off base to end the Gaels' first scoring threat.\u00a0 In the fourth, the Gaels put a pair on with two outs, but\nMason Ashlock\nturned what a appeared to be a line drive headed into the corner for extra bases and runs into an out with a diving stab to end the inning. Rice added two in the fifth thanks to back-to-back two-out doubles by Davis and Boehm and a single by Webb. The Owls added a sixth run when Robson's smash up the middle was flagged by SMC reliever Finn Chapman with runners and second and third with one out.\u00a0 Chapman threw home as Rios was attempting to score.\u00a0 In the ensuing rundown, Rios made it back to the bag and while the Gaels attempted to tag out trailing runner\nCole Green\n, Rios dashed home to score. The Gaels turned the game around with a six-run outburst in the bottom of the sixth, thanks to seven hits in the inning. Rice rebounded to retake the lead in the top of \u00a0the seventh on the Owls' third sacrifice fly of the day, this one courtesy Ashlock.\nPaul Smith's\ninfield single increased the Rice lead to 8-6, but Saint Mary's exploded for five runs in the bottom of the eighth and the game was called due to travel curfew.\nNext Up:\nRice returns home for a quick check in and laundry stop, hosting UTRGV on Tue day at 6:35 before heading back on the road next weekend to open American Conference play at South Florida.\nNotes\nRice has won three straight and nine of the last 11.\nThe Owls fell to 12-9 on the season, 6-6 on the road, and 5-2 at Brazell Field.\nKutter-Gage Webb\n(8) and\nGaret Boehm\n(7) combined for 15 RBI during the four games.\nColin Robson\nwas 5x17 with four doubles and reached base for the ninth consecutive game.\nMason Ashlock\nextended his hitting streak to six games."
